               <p>On the 20th of July, between nine and ten in the evening, upon <placeName id="t17760911-63-crimeloc313">Snow-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17760911-63-crimeloc313" type="placeName" value="Snow-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17760911-63-crimeloc313" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760911-63-off311 t17760911-63-crimeloc313"></join>, I felt a person at my pocket; I turned round and saw my handkerchief between the hand of the prisoner and the ground; I collared him, and took him to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17760911-63-person708">
                  JOHN
                   DARWELL
               <interp inst="t17760911-63-person708" type="surname" value="DARWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-63-person708" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-63-person708" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was coming down Snow-hill, and saw the prisoner take the handkerchief out of Mr. Hand's pocket; we secured him and delivered the handkerchief to the constable.</p>
               <p>[The handkerchief was produced in Court by 
               <persName id="t17760911-63-person709">
                  Thompson
               <interp inst="t17760911-63-person709" type="given" value="Thompson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760911-63-person709" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             the constable, and deposed to by the prosecutor.]</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>The handkerchief lay by me; I did not know who took it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17760911-63-verdict314" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17760911-63-verdict314" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the London Jury before Mr. RECORDER.</p>
